•   { N ≥ 0 } z,y,n:= true,-∞,0 { inv.n }

≡   Hoare triple

    N ≥ 0 ⇒ wp.(z,y,n:= true,-∞,0).(inv.n)

≡   Prove ⇒

    •   wp.(z,y,n:= true,-∞,0).(inv.n)

    (1) N ≥ 0

    ≡   Assignment

        (n ∈ [0,N] ∧ z ≡ p.n ∧ y = f.n)[z,y,n:= true,-∞,0]

    ≡   Textual substitution

        0 ∈ [0,N] ∧ true ≡ p.0 ∧ -∞ = f.0

    ≡   Membership; Theory [0,3]

        true

    ■

